audio_descriptions.notes:
Screen reads, "Dad Feels".
Act II, Part 28: Dad Elucidated.

Dad's empty computer desk, still scattered with various items, including a cell phone. Next to the desk is a sledgehammer, a wrapped package shaped like a sledgehammer, and a vacuum cleaner. There is a half-eaten pancake on the floor.
Dad enters, tucking in his shirt and straightening his tie.
Dad notices that the cell phone on his desk is playing music. He picks it up.
On the phone's small screen, Lazlo dances in front of a pink background.
Dad closes the phone.
Dad notices the pancake on the floor and picks it up.

Dad puts the pancake back on the floor and vacuums it up. It is sucked into the vacuum's internal canister.
Dad opens the canister and fishes the pancake out. It is still dirty.
Dad takes a bite out of the pancake.
Dad drops the pancake and looks around in confusion.
Now, Ella, a woman with short dark hair, works in a garden. She smiles.
She tends to small pink flowers.
Ella turns to the camera, surprised.
Now, Dad, who is seemingly named Andan, stands dazed next to the computer desk.
Now, in a flashback, light filters through white curtains. The camera pans down, revealing Ella sleeping, resting with her head against a window pane. The curtains rustle in the wind.
The shot changes to intermittently show Andan, who looks like Dad but with hair, sleeping against Ella's shoulder.
Now, Ella and Andan walk down the sidewalk in a suburban neighborhood, holding hands.
Now, Ella and Andan sit in front of their front door, talking. Ella laughs, and Andan smiles.
Now, Ella and Andan sit outside at night, lit by many small lamps. They look serious. Andan's arm is around Ella's shoulders. They look into each other's eyes.
Now, Ella sits at a dinner table. There are candles on the table, but the candles have small rings floating around the flames. Ella rests her cheek against her hand, looking down seriously.
Andan sits across the table, looking at Ella.
When Andan and Ella speak, their lips do not move.
Ella grimaces at Andan, then smiles.
We briefly see Andan sitting outside with Ella, hugging her.
They smile at each other, then Ella frowns.
We see the scenes with Andan and Ella move backward quickly, as if being rewound. It ends with Andan in a space suit, lying in a desert, before returning to Andan in the present, standing next to the computer desk.
Andan begins to walk away, stopping by the two sledgehammers. He touches the gift wrapped sledgehammer for a moment before picking up the unwrapped sledgehammer.
Andan leaves.
Mom enters with a paper bag.
Mom reaches into the paper bag and pulls out a motorcycle helmet.
Mom notices the pancake on the floor and picks it up.
Mom throws the pancake to the floor, looking panicked.
Mom runs off.
Now, we see the outside of a house surrounded by hedges. Mom runs to the front door.
After Mom bangs on the door, Neighbor comes out. Mom and Neighbor move their lips when they speak.
Mom's and Neighbor's lips no longer move.
Noise comes from inside Neighbor's house. They both look at the front door.
Neighbor, whose name is apparently Malvin, looks mildly surprised.
Malvin turns to go back inside, but Cheryl grabs him. She dips him and kisses him before pushing him back against the door. They stare at each other.
Malvin goes inside, and Cheryl runs off.
Shot pans to a nearby hedge. Carl emerges from behind the hedge.
Carl writes something down in his notepad. His lips move when he speaks.
Carl takes a bite out of a cinnamon bun and walks away. 
The shot pans up to the sky.
Now, in a flashback, Andan lies in his space suit in the desert.
Another person in a spacesuit stands over him before walking away.
Close up on Andan's hand, which twitches.
Now, the second figure is on a hill covered with small shrubs. The figure takes off their space suit, revealing a woman dressed all in white. 
Her shirt says "Lieutenant Emily Ridley" and has a logo that spells "D-A-D" in a stylized manner.
Emily's lips do not move when she speaks. She shields her eyes with her hand, then begins walking down the hill.
Emily stops by an empty road.
She sticks out her thumb to hitchhike.
Now, Andan, still dressed as Dad, stands holding his sledgehammer.
The shot pans out to show that he is standing on the roof of a huge tan building that says "YouTube" on it.
Cut to black.
Text reads, "The end."
Text changes to read, "The end of Act Two".
End card reads, "Dad merch. Link below" The screen cycles through a variety of Dad products, including shirts and hoodies. There are also now products with a "D-A-D" logo that appeared on Emily's shirt.
End card reads, "Subscribe to Dad. Twitter and Instagram at DadFeels. To be continued." There are video links to "Dad is Awake" and "Dad's Present from YouTube". There is also a link to Dad's gaming channel called "Dad Plays".
